    <h1>Medical Keywords &amp; Definitions</h1>
    <img src="/images-content/medical_terms.jpg" alt="Nurse writing on clipboard" class="imgRight" />
    <p><strong>Medical Data Backup Solution</strong> &ndash; Result of copying or archiving files and folders for the purpose of being able to restore them in case of <strong>data</strong> loss. <strong>Data</strong> loss can be caused by many things ranging from computer viruses to hardware failures to file corruption to fire, flood, or theft (etc).</p>
    <p><strong>Medical Information Technology and Medical IT</strong> &ndash; Intersection of healthcare and technology where skills in both medical and computer sciences come together in an effort to improve healthcare and patient outcomes. </p>
    <p><strong>Medical Technical Support</strong> &ndash; Technical support for medical field offices.</p>
    <p><strong>Risk Analysis</strong> &ndash; Process of aligning technology-related objectives with a company's business objectives.</p>
    <p><strong>Hipaa Compliance</strong> &ndash; Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act, sets the standard for protecting sensitive patient data. Any company that deals with protected health information (PHI) must ensure that all the required physical, network, and process security measures are in place and followed.</p>
    <p><strong>EMR</strong> &ndash; Electronic medical record is a digital version of a paper chart that contains all of a patient's medical history from one practice. </p>
    <p><strong>EHR</strong> &ndash; Electronic health record contain and share information from all providers involved in a patient's care.</p>
    <p><strong>Practice Management Software</strong> &ndash; (PMS) is a category of healthcare software that deals with the day-to-day operations of a medical practice that allows users to capture patient demographics, schedule appointments, maintain lists of insurance payors, perform billing tasks, and generate reports.</p>
    <p><strong>Meaningful Use</strong> &ndash; Improve quality, safety, efficiency, and reduce health disparities.</p>
    <p><strong>HIS or Hospital IT</strong> &ndash; A hospital information system (HIS) is an element of health informatics that focuses mainly on the administrational needs of hospitals.</p>
    <p><strong>Interface</strong> &ndash; Connect with (another computer or piece of equipment) by an interface.</p>
    <p><strong>End Of Life Equipment</strong> &ndash; Term used with respect to a product supplied to customers, indicating that the product is in the end of its useful life and a vendor stops marketing, selling, or rework sustaining it. </p>
    <p><strong>Phone System Compliance</strong> &ndash; State of being in accordance with established guidelines or specifications of HIPPA.</p>
    <p><strong>Patient Data</strong> &ndash; Data relating to a single patient, such as his/her diagnosis, name, age, earlier medical history etc.</p>
    <p><strong>Data Migration</strong> &ndash; Process of transferring data between computer storage types or file formats.</p>
    <p><strong>EMR Conversion</strong> &ndash; Act of switching medical records from paper to electronic or from one type of electronic storage software to another.</p>
